        "text": "Effect [ edit | edit source ] Body Press inflicts damage, but it uses the user's Defense stat instead of its Attack stat to calculate damage. The user's Defense stat stage-modifiers are applied (rather than Attack stage-modifiers), but otherwise its Attack modifiers are used (including held item , Ability , and burn ). For example, the user's Huge Power or a held Choice Band will increase the stat used in calculation, whereas Fur Coat or a held Eviolite will not. In the same vein, Slow Start or Defeatist can decrease the stat used in calculation, whereas Sword of Ruin cannot.",
